recalls.Summary: BMW of North America, LLC (BMW) is recalling certain 2018 BMW M5 vehicles.  In certain driving conditions, the engine control unit software may cause the fuel pump to stop.
recalls.Consequence: If the fuel pump stops, the vehicle will stall, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: BMW will notify owners, and dealers will update the engine control unit software, free of charge.  The recall began on June 25, 2018.  Owners may contact BMW customer service at 1-800-525-7417.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Component: BACK OVER PREVENTION: SENSING SYSTEM: CAMERA
recalls.Summary:
BMW of North America, LLC (BMW) is recalling certain 2018 540d, 2018-2020 530i, 530i xDrive, 540i, 540i xDrive, M550i xDrive, M5, 530e, 530e xDrive, X3 sDrive, X3 xDrive, X3 M40i, X3 M, and 2019-2020 X4 xDrive, X4 M40i, X4 M, X7 xDrive, X7 M50i, 740Li, 740Li xDrive, 750Li, 750Li xDrive, 8 Series Convertible and Coupe 840i, 840i xDrive, M850i xDrive, X5 sDrive, X5 xDrive, X5 M50i, X6 xDrive, X6 M50i, 330i, 330i xDrive, M340i, M340i xDrive, Z4 sDrive, Z4 M40i, 740Le xDrive and 745Le xDrive, 2018-2019 640i xDrive Gran Turismo and Rolls-Royce Phantom, 2019 M850i xDrive Gran Coupe and Rolls-Royce Cullinan and 2020 Toyota Supra vehicles.  

The back-up camera and display settings can be adjusted such that the rear view image is no longer visible and the system will retain that setting the next time the vehicle is placed in reverse.  As such, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard (FMVSS) number 111, "Rearview Mirrors."
recalls.Consequence: The lack of an image in the back-up camera display increases the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: BMW will notify owners, and dealers will update the back-up camera software, free of charge.  The recall began November 8, 2019.  Owners may contact BMW customer service at 1-800-525-7417 or Rolls-Royce at 1-877-877-3735.  Toyota owners may contact Toyota customer service at 1-888-270-9371.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: BMW of North America, LLC (BMW) is recalling certain 2018 BMW M5 vehicles.  The fuel level sensor in the fuel tank may become stuck against an in-tank fuel line, causing the fuel gauge to display an inaccurate and possibly larger amount of fuel than is actually available.
recalls.Consequence: An incorrect fuel reading may lead to the vehicle stalling and increase the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: BMW will notify owners, and dealers will secure the in-tank fuel line to keep the fuel line from contacting the fuel level sensor, free of charge.  The recall is expected to begin September 2018.  Owners may contact BMW customer service at 1-800-525-7417.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

complaints.summary: BMW issued a stop sale on 2017-2023 bmw F90 M5 chassis regarding the expansion tank failure. All vehicles should be affected by the recall. My current vehicle is experiencing the issues stated on the recall notice.  Expansion tank is failing and causing coolant to seep into engine bay

The coolant tank on my 2018 M5 failed causing a coolant leak. This is a highly documented problem on the forums and mine needed replacement at 22k miles. The bigger issue is the location of the tank because the coolant leaks on the ignition coils and fuel injectors causing failures later. My coils and spark plugs needed replacement along with the tank. This is unacceptable and BMW needs to address this issue.

This is for the front passenger seat only.The idrive system will give an error for the passenger restraint system and will mention there is a seat belt issue and turn off the airbag. This is intermittent and will happen with or without a passenger. I contacted BMW about it but because it is not presently acting out, they won't do anything about it unless I want to just start paying for new parts and do "exploratory" surgery on it trying to resolve this. Unacceptable as this has been happening for a couple of years and is a danger because of it happens during an accident it could prove fatal.

I ALMOST HAD A TERRIBLE ACCIDENT IN MY 2 WEEK OLD 2018 M5 ON THE 1-95 HIGHWAY ON THE NIGHT OF MAY 25, 2018 AT ABOUT 9:45PM. WITHOUT WARNING,  AT ABOUT 65MPH, THE CAR JERKED FOR ABOUT 3SECONDS , KICKED OUT OF DRIVE INTO NEUTRAL AND STARTED DECELERATING. I WAS IN THE MIDDLE LANE SURROUNDED BY SPEEDING VEHICLES. I MANAGED TO GUIDE IT TO THE SHOULDER AND TURNED OFF THE IGNITION FOR  2MINUTES, AFTER WHICH I RE-STARTED THE CAR AND WAS ABLE TO ENGAGE DRIVE. I CONTACTED MY DEALERSHIP TODAY, ONLY TO BE INFORMED, THIS WAS AS A RESULT OF COMPUTER GLITCH CONTROLLING THE FUEL PUMP CAUSING IT TO SHUT OFF WITHOUT WARNING. I WAS TOLD THERE HAS BEEN A SOFTWARE PATCH TO REMEDY THIS PROBLEM. IF IT IS TRUE, I BELIEVE THE CORRECTION SHOULD HAVE BEEN DONE BEFORE THE CAR WAS PICKED UP OR PROMPTLY NOTIFIED TO RETURN THE CAR FOR FIXING. I COULD HAVE BEEN KILLED ON THE HIGHWAY LAST NIGHT IF NOT FOR MY PROMPT SITUATION AWARENESS AND EXPERIENCE IN HANDLING THIS POWERFUL CAR WHICH IS MY FOURTH M5 SINCE 2006.   OWNERS NEED TO BE NOTIFIED IMMEDIATELY FOR FIXES LIKE THIS THAT CAN LEAD TO FATAL INCIDENTS. I DON'T KNOW IF ANYTHING SIMILAR HAS BEEN REPORTED ABOUT THIS MODEL

issues.title: High-Pressure Fuel Pump (HPFP) Failure
issues.description: The high-pressure fuel pump fails prematurely, causing fuel starvation under high load conditions. This is a known issue with the S63 V8 engine and can lead to complete loss of power.
symptoms: Loss of power at high RPM
issues.fix_description: Replace high-pressure fuel pump with updated part number and fuel pump control module software update
issues.prevention: Use high-quality fuel and avoid extended high-load driving when fuel level is low

issues.title: Turbocharger Wastegate Rattle
issues.description: The turbocharger wastegate actuators develop excessive play, causing a rattling noise especially during cold starts and low RPM operation.
symptoms: Rattling noise from engine bay on cold start
issues.fix_description: Replace turbocharger assembly or wastegate actuator depending on severity
issues.prevention: Allow proper engine warm-up and use recommended oil change intervals

issues.title: Active M Differential Failure
issues.description: The electronically controlled active M differential experiences pump failures and seal leaks, leading to loss of differential functionality and potential drivetrain damage.
issues.fix_description: Replace active differential pump, seals, or complete differential unit depending on failure mode
issues.prevention: Regular differential fluid changes and avoid aggressive launches on uneven surfaces

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Roof Delamination
issues.description: The carbon fiber roof panels experience delamination and clear coat failure, particularly on vehicles exposed to high UV conditions.
symptoms: Visible bubbling or peeling of roof surface
issues.fix_description: Roof panel replacement or professional refinishing depending on severity
issues.prevention: Park in covered areas when possible and use UV protection products

issues.title: Transmission Harsh Shifting and Jerking
issues.description: The 8-speed automatic transmission experiences harsh shifting, delayed engagement, and jerky operation, particularly in Sport+ mode.
issues.fix_description: Transmission software update, fluid change, or valve body replacement in severe cases
issues.prevention: Regular transmission fluid changes and avoid aggressive driving during warm-up

issues.title: Electronic Steering Column Lock Failure
issues.description: The electronic steering column lock mechanism fails, preventing the vehicle from starting or causing the steering to remain locked.
symptoms: Car won't start with steering lock warning
Steering wheel remains locked after starting
issues.fix_description: Replace electronic steering column lock module and reprogram with BMW diagnostic equipment
issues.prevention: Avoid turning steering wheel when vehicle is off and key is removed

issues.title: Crankshaft Position Sensor Failure
issues.description: The crankshaft position sensor fails intermittently, causing engine stalling, no-start conditions, and potential engine damage if not addressed promptly.
issues.fix_description: Replace crankshaft position sensor and clear fault codes
issues.prevention: Regular maintenance and prompt attention to check engine lights

issues.title: Brake Fluid Leak from ABS Module
issues.description: The ABS/DSC module develops internal leaks, causing brake fluid loss and potential brake failure. This is a safety-critical issue requiring immediate attention.
issues.fix_description: Replace ABS/DSC control module and bleed brake system completely
issues.prevention: Regular brake fluid changes and system inspections

issues.title: Instrument Cluster Pixel Failure
issues.description: The digital instrument cluster develops pixel failures and screen flickering, affecting readability of critical vehicle information.
issues.fix_description: Replace instrument cluster display unit and reprogram vehicle settings
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperature exposure and use sunshade when parked

issues.title: Engine Oil Consumption
issues.description: Excessive engine oil consumption beyond normal specifications, requiring frequent top-offs between service intervals.
issues.fix_description: Valve stem seal replacement, piston ring replacement, or engine rebuild depending on root cause
issues.prevention: Use BMW recommended oil grade and change intervals, avoid extended high-RPM operation when cold

issues.title: Adaptive LED Headlight Malfunction
issues.description: The adaptive LED headlight system experiences control module failures, causing headlights to malfunction or remain in safe mode with reduced functionality.
symptoms: One or both headlights not illuminating
issues.fix_description: Replace LED headlight control module or complete headlight assembly
issues.prevention: Avoid aftermarket HID/LED bulbs and protect from water damage during washing

issues.title: Coolant Pump Failure
issues.description: The electric coolant pump fails prematurely, leading to engine overheating and potential catastrophic engine damage if not addressed immediately.
issues.fix_description: Replace electric coolant pump and thermostat, flush cooling system
issues.prevention: Regular coolant system maintenance and prompt attention to temperature warnings

editorial.tagline: Executive sedan with supercar soul and M pedigree
editorial.hero_blurb: The F90 M5 Competition redefines the super sedan formula with 617 horsepower and all-wheel drive precision. This isn't just fast luxury—it's a technological tour de force that can embarrass supercars while hauling the family in supreme comfort.
editorial.essence: BMW's most potent production sedan ever built, the F90 M5 Competition represents the pinnacle of four-door performance engineering. It seamlessly blends everyday usability with track-day capability through sophisticated M xDrive all-wheel drive and relentless twin-turbo V8 power.
editorial.heritage: The M5 lineage dates to 1984 when BMW dropped their motorsport-derived M88 engine into the E28 5 Series. Through six generations, the M5 has consistently defined the high-performance luxury sedan segment, with the F90 representing the first all-wheel drive variant in the nameplate's storied 40-year history.
editorial.design_philosophy: BMW M's engineers pursued maximum performance without compromise, creating a sedan that could dominate both the Autobahn and Nürburgring while remaining refined enough for daily executive duties. The Competition variant strips away luxury features in favor of pure driving focus.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not directly race-bred like its predecessors, the F90 benefits from decades of M Division motorsport experience and serves as the basis for BMW's M5 CS—one of the fastest production sedans ever built around the Nürburgring.
editorial.engine_character: The S63 twin-turbo V8 delivers explosive, linear power with minimal turbo lag thanks to hot-vee turbocharger placement. It's a sophisticated brute that pulls relentlessly from 1,800 RPM to the 7,200 RPM redline with increasingly aggressive character as revs climb.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 8-speed M Steptronic transmission shifts with surgical precision in manual mode while providing seamless power delivery in automatic. Paddle shifts are lightning-quick with perfectly rev-matched downshifts that enhance the driving experience.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The adaptive M suspension and configurable M xDrive system create a chassis that can transform from comfortable cruiser to track weapon instantly. Body control is exceptional with minimal roll, while the rear-wheel drive modes unlock pure M5 character for enthusiasts.
editorial.steering_feel: Variable-ratio M steering provides excellent road feel and weighting that scales appropriately with drive modes. While not as communicative as hydraulic systems, it offers precise control and builds confidence through high-speed sweepers and tight corners alike.
editorial.brake_confidence: Massive M compound brakes with 6-piston front calipers provide tremendous stopping power with excellent pedal feel. The brakes resist fade even during aggressive track use while remaining progressive and easy to modulate in daily driving.
editorial.sound_signature: The S63 produces a distinctive growl that's both refined and menacing, with active exhaust valves creating dramatic sound changes between comfort and sport modes. Under full acceleration, it emits a spine-tingling roar that befits its 617-horsepower output.
editorial.ideal_owner: Performance enthusiasts who need four doors and luxury but refuse to compromise on driving dynamics. Perfect for executives who appreciate engineering excellence and want the fastest sedan money can buy.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Badge-conscious buyers seeking ultimate luxury, eco-conscious drivers, or those who prioritize fuel economy over performance. The Competition's firmer suspension may also displease comfort-first buyers.
editorial.buyers_summary: The F90 M5 Competition represents peak internal combustion performance in sedan form. While expensive to purchase and maintain, it delivers an unmatched combination of speed, sophistication, and everyday usability that defines the super sedan segment.

SUBJECT: BMW M5 F90 Competition (2018-2024), pristine showroom condition.

SETTING: Private collector's industrial warehouse garage. Brick warehouse with arched windows OR modern concrete gallery OR vintage factory with timber beams.

COMPOSITION: Front 3/4 hero angle showing front fascia and driver's side profile. Show COMPLETE car (all four wheels, both bumpers, full roofline). Camera at knee height.

LIGHTING: Golden hour sunlight streaming through large industrial windows. Warm color temperature. Cinematic depth.

TECHNICAL: Magazine-quality automotive photography. Photorealistic, no CGI look. No people, no text, no watermarks, no logos, no license plates.
